The paper focuses on studying road networks from an algorithmic perspective, specifically looking for properties that can be exploited in the design of fast algorithms. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions studying road networks as multiscale-dispersed graphs, which is a concept that can be related to data structures (cs.DS) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of Voronoi diagrams, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions that their algorithms can allow for non-metric weights, which is a concept that can be related to information theory (cs.IT).
